        <h2>Benefits of Healthy Eating</h2>

        <p>Healthy eating is essential for the functioning of our body, because it is from a balanced diet that we get the nutrients we need for our survival. A healthy diet is related to several benefits for our body, such as the improvement in immunity, mood and sleep quality, the increase in disposition, the regulation of our intestine, and the maintenance of weight.</p>
        <p>In addition, we must not forget that an unbalanced diet can help develop problems such as obesity, hyertension, diabetes, cardiovascular diseases, and even certain types of cancer. Investing in proper nutrition is, therefore, investing in your health.</p>
        <p>Surveys found that unhealthy diets were responsible for almost 11 million deaths in 2017, compared to 10.4 million deaths caused by high blood preassure and 8 million by cigarettes.</p>
        <h2>Obesity</h2>
        <p>The World Health Organization defines overweight and obesity as having excessive fat accumuation that presnts a risk to health.</p>
        <p>The WHO estimates that in 2019, 5 million deaths from noncommunicable diseases were caused by anhigh BMI, andrates of obesity continue to rise everyday worldwide.</p>
